<br>
I'm not sure whether I want to stay consistent with the comic style for the ad or beef it up a little.  I've had a few ideas for text, so that's subject to change, but go ahead and give suggestions if you want.  I'm mainly concerned about the characters and layout (haven't done ad's before), but whatever, go crazy, critique anything and everything.<br>
<br>
And if you think the comic style is a Mac Hall ripoff, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://students.washington.edu/durandal/shawisland/archive/20020716.htm">&quot;I may have used [it] as a launching pad for my own, but I assure you they're different.&quot;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  For instance, mine's worse.<br>
<br>
